To calculate Net Profit Margin:
1. Identify the Net Profit: $1,842,166.21
2. Identify the Total Revenue: $20,318,450.67
3. Calculate Net Profit Margin: (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

Net Profit Margin = ($1,842,166.21 / $20,318,450.67) × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 0.0906654 × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 9.07%

Therefore, the Net Profit Margin is 9.07%.
